### Authentication API - Request Examples
### Use VS Code REST Client extension to execute these requests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@email = test@example.com
@password = Password123!
@name = Test User

### 1. Check if API is working
GET {{baseUrl}}/

###

### 2. Create a new account
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-up/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "name": "{{name}}"
}

###

### 3. Login
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-in/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###

### 4. Check current session
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/session

###

### 5. Get authenticated user data (protected route)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/me

###

### 6. Get user profile (protected route)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/profile

###

### 7. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-out

###

### 8. Public route example
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/123

###

### 9. OpenAPI Documentation
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger
